{
  "texts": [
    "They present a viewpoint where Transformers can be viewed as a neural architecture operating on a complete graph.Viewing GNNs and Transformers as graph networks shows that they share a number of similarities.",
    "Both architectures take a set of values and decide how much different values should be considered when transforming them to update the values, with GNNs ignoring nodes that are not connected and Transformers scaling the importance of an input.",
    "It is worth noting that if the graph being processed by a GNN is a complete graph, the graph network will allow all nodes to have their messages propagated to one being updated.",
    "Therefore, it is possible to view the Transformer as a special case GNN operating on a complete graph.",
    "Whilst GNNs use the read module to take advantage of an underlying structure, the Transformer learns one based on the task.By applying a Transformer to a task, a graph structure is being learnt from scratch."
  ]
}